SIMPLE: magnum
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magnum
<hw>Mag"num</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧g"n⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Neut.
sing. of L. <ets>magnus</ets> great.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A large
wine bottle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They passed the <qex>magnum</qex> to one another freely.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A bone of the carpus at the base
of the third metacarpal bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A magnum pistol, or the cartridge such a pistol
uses; <as>as, he always carried a .44 <ex>magnum</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>magnum</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: magnum
<hw>mag"num</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧g"n⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Firearms)</fld> <def>Having a larger charge than usual for a
cartridge of the same caliber; -- of cartridges for handgun; <as>as, a
.44 <ex>magnum</ex> cartridge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Firearms)</fld> <def>Designed to use a cartridge
with a larger charge than usual for handguns of the same caliber; -- of
handguns; <as>as, a .44 <ex>magnum</ex> pistol</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>magnum opus</ent>⟦br⟧
